1
00:00:06,589 --> 00:00:10,176
CAGE

2
00:00:21,187 --> 00:00:22,105
<i>Kame-chan?</i>

3
00:00:23,440 --> 00:00:24,607
<i>Kame-chan?</i>

4
00:00:25,442 --> 00:00:26,693
<i>Kame-chan?</i>

5
00:00:27,861 --> 00:00:29,029
Kame-chan!

6
00:00:29,946 --> 00:00:31,865
You're up next, right?

7
00:00:34,284 --> 00:00:38,079
Sorry. I spaced out.

8
00:00:39,956 --> 00:00:42,250
Well, let's do this.

9
00:00:43,626 --> 00:00:45,295
Othello-kun.

10
00:00:46,129 --> 00:00:47,714
Finally.

11
00:00:51,050 --> 00:00:53,094
Togame-san, we've been waiting for this!

12
00:00:53,178 --> 00:00:54,262
Get him!

13
00:00:54,345 --> 00:00:55,597
Kill him!

14
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:57,390
Those are some intense cheers.

15
00:00:57,474 --> 00:00:59,184
Nothing compared to those before...

16
00:00:59,267 --> 00:01:01,186
Finish him with one punch!

17
00:01:04,481 --> 00:01:05,857
Sakura-san!

18
00:01:07,233 --> 00:01:09,110
Be careful out there!

19
00:01:09,194 --> 00:01:10,445
Don't die, okay?

20
00:01:10,528 --> 00:01:12,030
It's in your hands.

21
00:01:14,866 --> 00:01:15,992
Sakura.

22
00:01:17,243 --> 00:01:19,579
Go talk your heart out.

23
00:01:21,289 --> 00:01:24,083
<i>Fighting is a type of communication,
Sakura-kun.</i>

24
00:01:25,043 --> 00:01:27,420
<i>I don't know if that's even possible...</i>

25
00:01:28,296 --> 00:01:29,589
<i>Still...</i>

26
00:01:30,173 --> 00:01:33,843
<i>It's not just the usual excitement
I get from facing a strong opponent...</i>

27
00:01:34,594 --> 00:01:37,055
<i>I don't know what this feeling is called...</i>

28
00:01:38,681 --> 00:01:40,225
<i>But well...</i>

29
00:01:40,850 --> 00:01:43,853
I wish you luck on your fight tomorrow!

30
00:01:46,314 --> 00:01:49,192
<i>I did tell him to
"leave it to us," after all.</i>

31
00:01:50,693 --> 00:01:52,862
Let's get this started.

32
00:01:56,407 --> 00:01:59,077
There's no need to rush.

33
00:02:00,912 --> 00:02:05,083
Doing things fast
isn't necessarily a bad thing...

34
00:02:05,834 --> 00:02:09,295
but it can leave a lot to be desired,
don't you think?

35
00:02:10,547 --> 00:02:12,674
This time, especially...

36
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:16,803
I'd like to thoroughly enjoy this.

37
00:04:26,057 --> 00:04:29,519
<i>Sakura, I know that
you can put up quite a fight</i>

38
00:04:29,602 --> 00:04:32,230
<i>after watching you fight two days ago.</i>

39
00:04:32,313 --> 00:04:38,361
<i>But Togame is able to keep the devotees
of power, Shishitoren, under his control.</i>

40
00:04:39,112 --> 00:04:41,864
<i>That means he has the power to back it up.</i>

41
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:46,035
Although you said you wanted to take
it slow, you sure know how to move fast.

42
00:04:46,661 --> 00:04:49,414
Huh? You call <i>this</i> fast?

43
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:55,545
I'll toy with you slowly with this speed.

44
00:04:55,628 --> 00:04:57,046
Bring it on.

45
00:04:57,130 --> 00:04:59,173
I'll play along with your little game.

46
00:05:19,235 --> 00:05:22,697
Sakura-san's got his hands full
just dodging his attacks...

47
00:05:23,072 --> 00:05:28,286
Well, Togame and Tomiyama
have always been Shishitoren's best.

48
00:05:28,911 --> 00:05:30,288
That means...

49
00:05:30,830 --> 00:05:34,667
He's on a whole different level
from the earlier three.

50
00:05:36,127 --> 00:05:40,381
Well, I think his opponent
would understand that best.

51
00:05:47,430 --> 00:05:48,848
He got him!

52
00:05:52,810 --> 00:05:55,521
You've already matched up
to my speed, huh?

53
00:05:55,605 --> 00:05:57,231
You catch on fast, don't you?

54
00:06:01,986 --> 00:06:04,030
Say, Othello-kun...

55
00:06:04,113 --> 00:06:07,575
you called me lame
back at the tunnel, didn't you?

56
00:06:08,576 --> 00:06:11,954
That comment really pissed me off.

57
00:06:13,539 --> 00:06:19,087
And that... includes... the way... you talk!

58
00:06:28,554 --> 00:06:30,098
Way to go, Togame-san!

59
00:06:30,181 --> 00:06:31,682
Beat his ass!

60
00:06:31,766 --> 00:06:33,518
He's as damn strong as always!

61
00:06:33,893 --> 00:06:36,896
Kame-chan! Kame-chan!

62
00:06:40,858 --> 00:06:43,653
Huh? That's all you got?

63
00:06:44,654 --> 00:06:48,991
You're way more lame to me right now.

64
00:06:53,079 --> 00:06:57,583
The only people allowed to say
whatever they want and act all cocky

65
00:06:57,667 --> 00:07:01,003
are those with the power to back it up.

66
00:07:02,088 --> 00:07:07,510
You're only so smug because you've
wormed your way in with the strong.

67
00:07:09,137 --> 00:07:14,016
<i>Like how everything will fall silent
after you break the wind chime...</i>

68
00:07:14,892 --> 00:07:19,188
you can't talk any crap
when you're by yourself.

69
00:07:23,067 --> 00:07:24,944
Hey now.

70
00:07:25,027 --> 00:07:26,320
I'm still talki...

71
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:31,534
Yeah, you're right!

72
00:07:32,034 --> 00:07:35,037
Only those with power
are allowed to have freedom!

73
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:38,916
And if you don't have any power,
you can't push for what you believe in!

74
00:07:45,631 --> 00:07:50,887
But in your eyes... that's what I look like?

75
00:07:53,222 --> 00:07:54,932
<i>As the person...</i>

76
00:07:58,060 --> 00:08:00,021
<i>I hate the most.</i>

77
00:08:01,272 --> 00:08:03,399
In that case...

78
00:08:04,525 --> 00:08:06,903
I can't lose to you, even if it kills me.

79
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:23,920
What happened to that kid all of a sudden?

80
00:08:26,005 --> 00:08:29,175
<i>I knew that Sakura-san was strong, but...</i>

81
00:08:29,258 --> 00:08:31,302
<i>I didn't know he was this strong!</i>

82
00:08:32,428 --> 00:08:34,263
Come on, what's wrong?

83
00:08:35,306 --> 00:08:37,600
If you lose to me...

84
00:08:38,142 --> 00:08:41,938
that means you're wrong!

85
00:08:42,438 --> 00:08:46,692
If we apply that whole devotee crap
you scumbags so obsess about...

86
00:08:46,776 --> 00:08:48,861
isn't that right?

87
00:08:59,872 --> 00:09:02,124
Don't get ahead of yourself.

88
00:09:02,708 --> 00:09:03,793
You little brat!

89
00:09:13,052 --> 00:09:14,929
Devotee crap?

90
00:09:17,974 --> 00:09:21,018
You don't know anything about Shishitoren!

91
00:09:25,439 --> 00:09:29,360
Everyone in this room always
has their eyes on the top.

92
00:09:32,947 --> 00:09:35,866
They swore to stand
for what they believe in...

93
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:39,745
That's what it means to be
a devotee of power.

94
00:09:40,413 --> 00:09:43,082
Compared to you hero-wannabes...

95
00:09:44,959 --> 00:09:48,129
the weight of our power is far heavier!

96
00:09:49,922 --> 00:09:51,674
{\an8}He won't be able to stand up!

97
00:09:51,757 --> 00:09:53,593
{\an8}Now you know how strong Togame-san is!

98
00:09:56,804 --> 00:09:59,724
Sakura-san, no way...

99
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,601
Not yet.

100
00:10:02,602 --> 00:10:04,520
Like I said...

101
00:10:04,604 --> 00:10:05,980
You aren't doin'...

102
00:10:07,064 --> 00:10:10,234
what you're preachin'.

103
00:10:11,193 --> 00:10:15,990
You better change your goddamn
name to "Our Little Bully Club"!

104
00:10:16,741 --> 00:10:19,619
Stop talking.

105
00:10:19,702 --> 00:10:24,373
I'd never lose to scumbags
who'd beat up a guy who's already down...

106
00:10:26,417 --> 00:10:29,962
<i>Not to scumbags who'd chase around
an innocent middle school kid...</i>

107
00:10:32,214 --> 00:10:35,384
Never!

108
00:10:48,898 --> 00:10:50,274
What's that?

109
00:10:51,108 --> 00:10:52,902
I never heard about that.

110
00:10:53,569 --> 00:10:55,363
I see.

111
00:10:56,113 --> 00:10:58,532
So that's why you two were there?

112
00:11:03,663 --> 00:11:05,581
Give me a second.

113
00:11:10,252 --> 00:11:12,880
To be frank, I did find it odd.

114
00:11:12,963 --> 00:11:16,050
Why would Furin trespass
on our turf for no reason?

115
00:11:18,135 --> 00:11:20,388
What did you two do back there?

116
00:11:22,014 --> 00:11:23,224
Answer me.

117
00:11:24,433 --> 00:11:28,312
We saw an unfamiliar middle school kid,
so we thought we'd play with him a bit...

118
00:11:28,396 --> 00:11:31,774
But Saruwatari was the one
who suggested it first.

119
00:11:52,420 --> 00:11:54,296
Aw, Kame-chan!

120
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:56,799
Forget about those two,
and get back to the fight!

121
00:11:57,383 --> 00:11:59,385
Things were just getting good!

122
00:12:07,351 --> 00:12:09,895
Sorry about that.

123
00:12:09,979 --> 00:12:12,314
Thanks for waiting.

124
00:12:15,276 --> 00:12:18,070
Let's... continue.

125
00:13:09,330 --> 00:13:11,373
Oh, wow!

126
00:13:11,457 --> 00:13:13,626
You took them all down by yourself?

127
00:13:15,252 --> 00:13:16,837
You're strong!

128
00:13:24,011 --> 00:13:26,764
What do you say? Will you join our team?

129
00:13:28,599 --> 00:13:29,642
Huh?

130
00:13:29,725 --> 00:13:30,893
What are you sa...

131
00:13:30,976 --> 00:13:33,020
Our team's name is Shishitoren!

132
00:13:33,103 --> 00:13:34,855
No, I mean...

133
00:13:35,523 --> 00:13:39,777
I just joined myself,
but I'm sure you'll like it!

134
00:13:39,860 --> 00:13:42,488
Wait, hold on a minu...

135
00:13:42,863 --> 00:13:46,116
Come with me!
I'll introduce you to everyone!

136
00:13:50,162 --> 00:13:53,415
<i>That's how I met Choji.</i>

137
00:14:47,011 --> 00:14:50,431
Do you know what "devotees of power"
actually means?

138
00:14:51,473 --> 00:14:53,767
Hey, hey! Kame-chan! Kame-chan!

139
00:14:53,851 --> 00:14:55,728
You hear me? Do you know what it means?

140
00:14:56,353 --> 00:14:58,814
{\an8}Yeah, I heard you and I know.

141
00:14:58,898 --> 00:15:00,774
{\an8}They told me when I joined.

142
00:15:00,858 --> 00:15:02,067
{\an8}So, so!

143
00:15:02,151 --> 00:15:06,238
{\an8}It means a vow not to succumb
to anyone and to push ourselves!

144
00:15:06,864 --> 00:15:10,743
You really never listen
to other people, huh?

145
00:15:11,827 --> 00:15:15,873
They say power is
what we use to attain freedom!

146
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:22,254
The newbies that recently joined
are really something else!

147
00:15:22,338 --> 00:15:23,881
Yeah, I heard about them!

148
00:15:23,964 --> 00:15:27,927
<i>They raided Zinc on their own
and beat them to a plump, right?</i>

149
00:15:28,010 --> 00:15:30,095
<i>Everyone's talking about them.</i>

150
00:15:32,264 --> 00:15:33,641
We're back!

151
00:15:34,183 --> 00:15:36,769
We beat the crap out of them
for you, Numa-chan!

152
00:15:40,314 --> 00:15:42,524
Thanks.

153
00:15:43,484 --> 00:15:45,945
You guys seriously raided them?

154
00:15:46,028 --> 00:15:47,488
You two are amazing.

155
00:15:47,655 --> 00:15:48,656
{\an8}HMPH

156
00:15:48,739 --> 00:15:51,700
{\an8}I got my eyes set on being
the freest person here, after all!

157
00:15:51,784 --> 00:15:53,869
{\an8}I'm losing now!

158
00:16:01,043 --> 00:16:04,171
When we first joined the team,

159
00:16:04,254 --> 00:16:07,216
they taught us that
power is a means to be free, right?

160
00:16:07,716 --> 00:16:13,847
So he's saying that the strongest
person would be the most free.

161
00:16:14,723 --> 00:16:15,849
Right?

162
00:16:15,933 --> 00:16:17,017
Yup, yup!

163
00:16:17,101 --> 00:16:20,229
Being the freest person
sounds fun, doesn't it?

164
00:16:20,312 --> 00:16:23,399
I'm competing with Kame-chan
to see who'll get there first!

165
00:16:25,067 --> 00:16:27,486
You should all join us! Let's all race!

166
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:30,572
<i>Back then, Choji was really strong</i>

167
00:16:30,656 --> 00:16:32,992
<i>and was enjoying his life
more than anyone else.</i>

168
00:16:33,575 --> 00:16:36,453
<i>He was the very embodiment
of our devotion.</i>

169
00:16:36,537 --> 00:16:38,372
<i>He was like the sun.</i>

170
00:16:39,456 --> 00:16:41,750
<i>Choji called it a race.</i>

171
00:16:41,834 --> 00:16:44,253
<i>But I never intended to race with him.</i>

172
00:16:44,837 --> 00:16:48,215
<i>I had always found it difficult
to hang out with other people...</i>

173
00:16:48,298 --> 00:16:51,677
<i>but when I was with Choji,
I was able to blend in with everyone.</i>

174
00:16:53,470 --> 00:16:55,097
<i>It was fun.</i>

175
00:16:56,765 --> 00:16:59,184
<i>It really did feel
like we'd attained freedom.</i>

176
00:17:02,813 --> 00:17:05,524
<i>If Choji could become our leader...</i>

177
00:17:05,607 --> 00:17:09,528
<i>I was certain that the team
would grow into something even better.</i>

178
00:17:13,574 --> 00:17:15,075
<i>Or so I thought.</i>

179
00:17:36,263 --> 00:17:37,431
Choji?

180
00:17:37,514 --> 00:17:39,433
What's the matter?

181
00:17:41,268 --> 00:17:43,937
-Come inside with everyone...
-Hey, Kame-chan.

182
00:17:44,021 --> 00:17:47,191
I've reached the top, haven't I?

183
00:17:49,485 --> 00:17:50,402
Yeah.

184
00:17:51,445 --> 00:17:55,699
The top is someone who's
the strongest and the most free, right?

185
00:17:57,618 --> 00:17:58,660
Yeah.

186
00:18:00,454 --> 00:18:03,332
But it's not fun at all...

187
00:18:10,631 --> 00:18:13,842
So I had an idea...

188
00:18:15,010 --> 00:18:20,432
I just have to make the whole team
just as strong as I am.

189
00:18:27,523 --> 00:18:31,068
Oh, so you want to train everyone, right?

190
00:18:32,820 --> 00:18:34,196
I think that's a great idea.

191
00:18:34,696 --> 00:18:36,240
Let's tell everyone insi-

192
00:18:36,365 --> 00:18:37,950
Tomiyama-san! Togame-san!

193
00:18:42,412 --> 00:18:45,082
Zinc attacked him just now.

194
00:18:46,041 --> 00:18:48,377
Zinc? Them again?

195
00:18:48,961 --> 00:18:50,295
Let's go, Choji...

196
00:19:10,524 --> 00:19:13,485
You came back after getting
your ass handed to you?

197
00:19:14,528 --> 00:19:16,029
Don't do that.

198
00:19:16,113 --> 00:19:18,699
You won't get stronger that way.

199
00:19:19,283 --> 00:19:22,202
You can't be free that way.

200
00:19:22,286 --> 00:19:23,704
It's not fun.

201
00:19:25,330 --> 00:19:26,915
The weak...

202
00:19:31,253 --> 00:19:34,173
have no place in Shishitoren.

203
00:19:39,636 --> 00:19:41,555
Isn't that right,

204
00:19:41,638 --> 00:19:43,056
Kame-chan?

205
00:19:46,226 --> 00:19:47,477
Why?

206
00:19:48,562 --> 00:19:50,063
What makes you think so?

207
00:19:50,147 --> 00:19:53,317
-Doing that won't make anyone stro...
-I'm the leader, right?

208
00:19:56,028 --> 00:19:58,655
I'm the strongest one around.

209
00:19:58,739 --> 00:20:00,157
I'm free.

210
00:20:00,908 --> 00:20:02,910
I won't submit to anyone.

211
00:20:02,993 --> 00:20:04,453
I decide things around here.

212
00:20:05,579 --> 00:20:07,706
If you won't listen, then leave.

213
00:20:17,799 --> 00:20:19,134
Fine.

214
00:20:20,219 --> 00:20:21,345
But...

215
00:20:23,430 --> 00:20:27,476
I'll be the one to tell everyone
about your plans, Choji.

216
00:20:28,977 --> 00:20:31,313
I'll be the one to rip off their skins.

217
00:20:34,107 --> 00:20:36,026
So, Choji...

218
00:20:37,653 --> 00:20:39,780
Please keep smiling with everyone.

219
00:20:41,615 --> 00:20:43,659
<i>I decided to take the fall.</i>

220
00:20:46,995 --> 00:20:49,748
<i>The sun has to be loved by everyone.</i>

221
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:55,963
<i>Even if it means tying everyone down
with this power to attain freedom...</i>

222
00:20:57,631 --> 00:21:00,717
<i>I will preserve the current Shishitoren.</i>

223
00:21:02,302 --> 00:21:03,929
<i>Until the sun...</i>

224
00:21:05,305 --> 00:21:07,099
<i>shows itself again.</i>

225
00:21:22,281 --> 00:21:23,573
Are you serious?

226
00:21:23,657 --> 00:21:25,033
You're kidding me!

227
00:21:27,452 --> 00:21:30,372
You aren't going all-out, aren't you?

228
00:21:31,456 --> 00:21:35,168
-Huh? That's not wh...
-You aren't even trying to hit me.

229
00:21:35,252 --> 00:21:37,879
And you're not even trying
to dodge my kicks.

230
00:21:39,798 --> 00:21:42,634
Just what the hell are you trying to do?

231
00:21:51,310 --> 00:21:53,437
Yeah, really...

232
00:21:54,187 --> 00:21:56,565
just what am I trying to do?

233
00:23:31,159 --> 00:23:33,370
{\an8}The sound of the impact
from Togame-san's geta

234
00:23:33,453 --> 00:23:36,790
{\an8}was nothing like you'd expect
coming from wood.

235
00:23:36,873 --> 00:23:39,042
{\an8}From how it felt
when he hit me on the head,

236
00:23:39,126 --> 00:23:41,294
{\an8}it doesn't seem to have any metal inside.

237
00:23:41,378 --> 00:23:43,338
{\an8}You can tell from that?

238
00:23:43,964 --> 00:23:47,509
{\an8}Well, I've got my head hit with
numerous stuff before, after all.

239
00:23:48,385 --> 00:23:50,011
{\an8}-For example...
-For example?

240
00:23:50,095 --> 00:23:52,347
{\an8}-This.
-This?

241
00:23:52,430 --> 00:23:53,598
{\an8}Or this.

242
00:23:53,682 --> 00:23:54,724
{\an8}This too?

243
00:23:54,808 --> 00:23:55,892
{\an8}And even this!

244
00:23:58,728 --> 00:23:59,896
{\an8}So scary...

